[thinking] **Evaluating native image issues**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m noticing a potential problem with the Native Image regarding unsupported defineClass and loading classes from resources post-build. That makes me wonder if Class.getResourceAsStream needs resource configuration in the image. They seem to generate this config from tests, which is interesting. Since we can't modify the native config, I'm curious about how tests should run under Native Image. It seems like we’re dealing with open-ended dynamic class loading here. The class definitions are there, but they’re read at runtime.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Considering error handling in runtime**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking that new classes at runtime might lead to an UnsupportedFeatureError. The rule seems to be that if it fundamentally requires dynamic class loading, I should catch the Error, verify it with NativeImageSupport, and then rethrow if it doesn’t match. It looks like I can't rethrow if it's supported. So, I can catch the Error in test code invoking Loader’s dynamic define. I might need to import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport for this. I'll look into it!
[thinking] 
